00032 #define DEFAULT_CYCLE_S 30
00033 #define DEFAULT_CYCLE_GEARS 6
00034 #define US_TO_SEC 1000000
00035 
00036 /// The void * generator for cycle
00037 struct cycle_gen {
00038     float cycle_length; // Time for a complete cycle
00039     struct timeval firsttime; // The last first that we pulled values
00040     unsigned char gears; // Time through current cycle
00041 };
00042 
00043 const char *cycle_simgen_name() {
00044     return "Cycle";
00045 }

00047 const char *cycle_simgen_longdesc() {
00048     return "Cycle through a wide range of valid OBDII values\n"
00049         "Seed: [cycle-length-in-seconds[,number-of-gears]]";
00050 }

00052 int cycle_simgen_create(void **gen, const char *seed) {
00053     struct cycle_gen *g = (struct cycle_gen *)malloc(sizeof(struct cycle_gen));
00054     if(NULL == g) {
00055         fprintf(stderr, "Couldn't allocate memory for cycle generator\n");
00056         return 1;
00057     }
00058 
00059     g->cycle_length = DEFAULT_CYCLE_S;
00060     gettimeofday(&g->firsttime, NULL);
00061     g->gears = DEFAULT_CYCLE_GEARS;
00062 
00063     if(NULL != seed && '\0' != *seed) {
00064         char *seedcpy = strdup(seed);
00065         
00066         char *tok = strtok(seedcpy, ", ");
00067         if(NULL != tok) {
00068             int t = atoi(tok);
00069             if(0 < t) {
00070                 g->cycle_length = t;
00071                 printf("Setting cycle length to %i seconds\n", t);
00072             }
00073 
00074             tok = strtok(NULL, ", ");
00075             if(NULL != tok) {
00076                 int gears = atoi(tok);
00077                 if(0 < gears) {
00078                     g->gears = gears;
00079                     printf("Setting gears to %i\n", g->gears);
00080                 }
00081             }
00082         }
00083         free(seedcpy);
00084     }
00085 
00086     *gen = g;
00087     return 0;
00088 }

00090 void cycle_simgen_destroy(void *gen) {
00091     free(gen);

00094 int cycle_simgen_getvalue(void *gen, unsigned int mode, unsigned int PID, unsigned int *A, unsigned int *B, unsigned int *C, unsigned int *D) {
00095 
00096     struct cycle_gen *g = (struct cycle_gen *)gen;
00097 
00098     if(0x00 == PID || 0x20 == PID || 0x40 == PID) {
00099         *A = 0xFF;
00100         *B = 0xFF;
00101         *C = 0xFF;
00102         *D = 0x40==PID?0xFE:0xFF;
00103         return 4;
00104     }
00105 
00106     if(0x60 <= PID) return 0;
00107 
00108     struct timeval newtime;
00109     gettimeofday(&newtime, NULL);
00110 
00111     float dt = (newtime.tv_sec - g->firsttime.tv_sec)
00112                 + ((float)((long)newtime.tv_usec - (long)g->firsttime.tv_usec) / (float)US_TO_SEC);
00113 
00114     if(dt < 0) {
00115         printf("Cycle dt<0! dt: %f , newtime: %li %li , firsttime: %li %li\n",
00116                         dt,
00117                         (long)newtime.tv_sec, (long)newtime.tv_usec,
00118                         (long)g->firsttime.tv_sec, (long)g->firsttime.tv_usec
00119                         );
00120         dt = 0; // Kluuuuudge
00121     }
00122 
00123     while(dt > g->cycle_length) {
00124         dt -= g->cycle_length;
00125     }
00126 
00127     struct obdservicecmd *cmd = obdGetCmdForPID(PID);
00128     if(NULL == cmd || NULL == cmd->convrev) {
00129         return 0;
00130     }
00131     float min = cmd->min_value;
00132     float max = cmd->max_value;
00133     OBDConvRevFunc conv = cmd->convrev;
00134 
00135     float cyclefraction = dt/g->cycle_length;
00136     float val = min + cyclefraction * (max-min);
00137 
00138     // RPM gets special treatment
00139     if(NULL != cmd->db_column && 0 != strcmp(cmd->db_column, "rpm")) {
00140         if(NULL == conv) return cmd->bytes_returned; // Can't usefully convert
00141         return conv(val, A, B, C, D);
00142     } else {
00143         int rpm_min = 500;
00144         int rpm_range = 6000;
00145         // int curr_gear = (int)(g->gears * cyclefraction);
00146 
00147         float revs = (g->gears * rpm_range) * cyclefraction;
00148         while(revs > rpm_range) {
00149             revs -= rpm_range;
00150         }
00151         revs += rpm_min;
00152 
00153         // fprintf(stderr, "rpm=%f, dt=%f\n", revs, dt);
00154         if(NULL == conv) return 0; // Can't usefull convert
00155         return conv(revs, A, B, C, D);
00156     }
00157 
00158     return -1; // Shouldn't be able to get here
00159 }
